---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Privacy Policy";
const metaDescription = "Read the Gutter Cleaners Uxbridge privacy policy to understand how we collect, use, and protect your personal data.";
const canonical = "https://www.guttercleanersuxbridge.co.uk/privacy-policy/";
---

<Layout title={title} description={metaDescription} canonical={canonical}>
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-blue-900 to-blue-800 text-white py-12">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-blue-100">Last updated: 1 July 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 sm:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-slate">
      <p>
        Gutter Cleaners Uxbridge ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy
        explains what personal data we collect when you use our website or request a quote, why we collect
        it, and how we use it.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>When you submit a quote request through our website, we collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Name</li>
        <li>Phone number</li>
        <li>Email address (optional)</li>
        <li>Property address and postcode</li>
        <li>Details about the service you're enquiring about</li>
        <li>Any additional message you provide</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We also collect standard technical information automatically, such as your IP address and browser
        type, to help us secure our website and understand how it's used.
      </p>

      <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use the information you provide to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to your quote request and arrange a survey or service</li>
        <li>Communicate with you about your enquiry or booking</li>
        <li>Improve our website and services</li>
        <li>Comply with our legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not sell your personal data to third parties.</p>

      <h2>Data Storage &amp; Security</h2>
      <p>
        Quote request data is stored securely using Cloudflare's infrastructure. We take reasonable
        technical and organisational measures to protect your data against unauthorised access, loss, or
        misuse.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We use Google Analytics to understand how visitors use our site. This may involve cookies that
        collect anonymised usage data. You can opt out of Google Analytics tracking using your browser
        settings or available opt-out browser extensions.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Request access to the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
        <li>Object to or restrict how we process your data</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain quote request data only as long as necessary to respond to your enquiry and meet our
        legal and accounting obligations, after which it is securely deleted.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with
        an updated revision date.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this privacy policy or how we handle your data, please
        <a href="/contact/">get in touch</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
